info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 16 at 3:39AM EST until November 16 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Key West
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 AM EST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...East winds of 30 to 40 mph with gusts of 50 to 60 mph. * WHERE...Eastern Upper Florida Keys near North Key Largo and Ocean Reef. * WHEN...Until 7 AM EST this morning. * IMPACTS...A High Wind Warning means that sustained winds of 40 mph or greater are expected. Scattered power outages will be possible. Winds this strong will make driving difficult, especially for high profile and small vehicles. Wind gusts along the Overseas Highway will be highest on bridges and overpasses.
info.instruction: Motorists should be alert for strong winds and sudden wind gusts, especially on bridges, which may cause you to lose control of your vehicle. Avoid travel if possible, and use extreme caution if you must drive. Residents should secure trash cans, lawn furniture, and other loose or lightweight outdoor objects.
